  "local_port": 41102,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I apply driving license in Bangalore?",
  "response": "Applying for a driving license in Bangalore involves several steps. Here is a detailed guide to help you through the process:\n\n### Step 1: Learner\u2019s License\nBefore applying for a permanent driving license, you need to obtain a learner\u2019s license.\n\n**Eligibility**\n- **Age:** \n  - 16 years for a two-wheeler (without gear)\n  - 18 years for a motor vehicle (with gear)\n  - 20 years for commercial vehicle\n\n**Documents Required**\n- Age proof (birth certificate, school certificate, passport, or PAN card)\n- Address proof (Aadhaar card, passport, utility bills, or rental agreement)\n- Form 1 (declaration of physical fitness)\n- Form 2 (application form for the learner's license)\n- Passport-sized photographs\n\n**Procedure**\n1. **Online Application:** Visit the [Parivahan Sewa](https://parivahan.gov.in/parivahan/) website.\n   - Fill in Form 2 online.\n   - Upload the required documents.\n   - Book an appointment for the test.\n2. **Offline Application:** Visit the nearest Regional Transport Office (RTO).\n   - Fill in Form 2 (available at the RTO or can be downloaded from the Parivahan Sewa website).\n   - Submit the documents.\n   - Pay the fee and schedule the test.\n\n**Learner\u2019s License Test**\n- Attend the test on the scheduled date.\n- The test usually involves basic questions about traffic rules and regulations.\n\n### Step 2: Permanent Driving License\nAfter holding the learner's license for at least 30 days and within 180 days, you can apply for the permanent driving license.\n\n**Eligibility**\n- Must hold a valid learner's license.\n- Should have practiced driving for at least 30 days.\n\n**Documents Required**\n- Learner\u2019s license\n- Form 4 (application for driving license)\n- Form 5 (training certificate from a driving school, if applicable for commercial vehicles)\n- Passport-sized photographs\n- If applying for a transport vehicle license, Form 15 (driving certificate from a driving school)\n\n**Procedure**\n1. **Online Application:** Visit the [Parivahan Sewa](https://parivahan.gov.in/parivahan/) website. \n   - Fill in Form 4 online. \n   - Upload the required documents.\n   - Book an appointment for the driving test.\n2. **Offline Application:** Visit the RTO with all required documents. \n   - Fill in Form 4.\n   - Submit the documents.\n   - Pay the fee and schedule the driving test.\n\n**Driving Test**\n- Attend the driving test on the scheduled date.\n- The test generally involves driving on a track and demonstrating various driving skills, such as parking, reversing, and turning.\n\n**Post-Test**\n- Once you pass the driving test, your biometric information will be collected.\n- The permanent driving license will be sent to your registered address via post.\n\n### Tips\n- Ensure all documents are valid and correctly filled out.\n- Practice driving adequately before attempting the test.\n- Be punctual and polite during the test and interactions with RTO officials.\n\nRemember to monitor your application status online and follow up if there are any delays in receiving your license.",
